Message:
"Disable exponential stepping in synthetic scenes (aabb=1) by default

- Makes only a small performance difference (~20%) and matches original NeRF behavior. Remove the need for --nerf_compatibility when wanting to draw rough parallels to original NeRF.
- Also adds a GUI slider to adjust cone tracing angle live."
"Use row-major encoding when possible to improve perf and memory"
"Significant memory reduction through TCNN's new arena"
"Speed up NeRF by 10-20% through SoA dir encoding"
"Optimize SDF & NeRF through SoA memory layout"

"Base extrinsics optimization LR decay on the respective optimizer's step count rather than the global one

Gradually growing datasets thus allow extrinsics learning of new images while old ones stay put"
"Exposure density range parameter when saving a density grid to PNG"
"Vulkan: more robust validation layer setup and logging"
"Reduce GPU RAM footprint of jpg/png datasets by 2x"
"Liberal use of `fmt::format` rather than string concatenation"

"Improve performance in large scene by ~10%

Makes more aggressive use of the occupancy bitfield when rendering"
"DLSS: allow more extensive dynamic resolution scaling"
"DLSS: default to on (now that dynamic res works better)"
"Make SDF and NeRF tracer allocations temporary (reduces overall memory consumption)"
"Increase GPU usage (and thus performance) for lower resolution rendering"
"GUI: make lines twice as thick (much easier to see)"
"More robust mechanism to find the binary root dir"
"SDF: faster ray stabbing when OptiX is not found"
"VR: better performance settings handling & disable DLSS with passthrough"
"VR: fix not all performance settings being applied when starting with `--vr`"
"Optimise global average pooling on GPU implementation."
"added initial code, some pairwise computation stuff"
"changed to use matrix multiplication instead of multiple vector multiplications"
"Added momentum. Loss seems to be monotonically increasing."
"tentative code to compute and sort by morton codes"
"Perplexity Search with OOM on large inputs"
"Pulled sparsity scaling back to theoretic limit."
"Added a lot of new symmetrization code"
